[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now Sarai,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Abram’s wife, had not given birth to any children,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but she had an Egyptian servant"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " named Hagar."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Sarai said to Abram, “Since"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has prevented me from having children, have sexual relations with"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my servant. Perhaps I can have a family by her.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Abram did what"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Sarai told him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So after Abram had lived"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in Canaan for ten years, Sarai, Abram’s wife, gave Hagar, her Egyptian servant,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to her husband to be his wife."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He had sexual relations with"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Hagar, and she became pregnant."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Once Hagar realized she was pregnant, she despised Sarai."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Sarai said to Abram, “You have brought this wrong on me!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I allowed my servant to have sexual relations with you,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but when she realized"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that she was pregnant, she despised me."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " May the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " judge between you and me!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Abram said to Sarai, “Since your"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " servant is under your authority,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " do to her whatever you think best.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Sarai treated Hagar"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " harshly,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so she ran away from Sarai."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "s angel"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " found Hagar near a spring of water in the desert – the spring that is along the road to Shur."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He said, “Hagar, servant of Sarai, where have you come from, and where are you going?” She replied, “I’m running away from"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my mistress, Sarai.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "s angel said to her, “Return to your mistress and submit"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to her authority. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I will greatly multiply your descendants,” the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "s angel added,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “so that they will be too numerous to count.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "s angel said to her,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“You are now"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " pregnant"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and are about to give birth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to a son."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "You are to name him Ishmael,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "for the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has heard your painful groans."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He will be a wild donkey"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of a man."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "He will be hostile to everyone,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and everyone will be hostile to him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "He will live away from"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his brothers.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Hagar named the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who spoke to her, “You are the God who sees me,”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for she said, “Here I have seen one who sees me!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " That is why the well was called"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Beer Lahai Roi."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (It is located"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " between Kadesh and Bered.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Hagar gave birth to Abram’s son, whom Abram named Ishmael."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " (Now"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Abram was 86 years old"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " when Hagar gave birth to Ishmael.)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]